Seven major U.S. farm group unusual step release joint statement urge congressional leader tinker exist farm law. Following meeting House Agriculture Committee Chairman Kika de la Garza (D-Tex.) Senate Agriculture Committee Chairman Patrick Leahy (D-Vt.) group issue statement say lawmaker "resist effort overhaul 15-month-old law operating crop marketing year." The farm group include American Farm Bureau Federation American Soybean Association National Cattlemen's Association National Corn Growers Association National Cotton Council National Pork Producers Council U.S. Rice Producers Legislative Group. The statement Congress modify 1985 farm bill "so law intend impact make agriculture competitive export market maintain farm income." "We strongly believe American farmer predictability certainty farm legislation opportunity make proper production marketing decisions" group said. Reuter 